<exercise checkit-seed="0008" checkit-slug="L2" checkit-title="Truth Tables">
    <statement>
        <p>
            Construct a truth table for the following formula. Make sure your table is in the standard order and that you have included all the necessary intermediate columns.
        </p>
        <me>(Q \rightarrow \sim R) \wedge (P \rightarrow R)</me>
    </statement>
    <answer>
        <p>
            The first and final columns of the truth table are
        </p>
        <m>
        \begin{array}{lllcc} P &amp; Q &amp; R &amp; \cdots &amp; \text{Final Column} \\ \hline \text{True} &amp; \text{True} &amp; \text{True} &amp; \cdots &amp; \text{False} \\ \text{True} &amp; \text{True} &amp; \text{False} &amp; \cdots &amp; \text{False} \\ \text{True} &amp; \text{False} &amp; \text{True} &amp; \cdots &amp; \text{True} \\ \text{True} &amp; \text{False} &amp; \text{False} &amp; \cdots &amp; \text{False} \\ \text{False} &amp; \text{True} &amp; \text{True} &amp; \cdots &amp; \text{False} \\ \text{False} &amp; \text{True} &amp; \text{False} &amp; \cdots &amp; \text{True} \\ \text{False} &amp; \text{False} &amp; \text{True} &amp; \cdots &amp; \text{True} \\ \text{False} &amp; \text{False} &amp; \text{False} &amp; \cdots &amp; \text{True} \\ \end{array}
        </m>
        <p>
            Recall that <m>\vee</m> means "or," <m>\wedge</m> means "and," and <m>\sim</m> means "not."
        </p>
    </answer>
</exercise>
